{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1b440e57-75a0-4101-9e3b-922c61adad9e","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nKey difference: xUnit embeds the skip reason directly in the `[Fact]`/`[Theory]` attribute rather than using a separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4ac57d61-5740-4618-9f8d-ef97a9de7e9f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":310,"requestId":"340D:322A6C:A67D5C:C2E493:69F3FF13"},"id":"d2bed73e-ff6e-47a9-863b-c8c2e4dbeaf3","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:17:14.660Z","parentId":"b3ca5364-aa3b-4d35-97dc-572b32ab4338"}
